Package com.cafean.CodePlugins

Class MECodePlugin

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.cafean.CodePlugins.MEPlugin
      • com.cafean.CodePlugins.MECodePlugin
  • public abstract class MECodePlugin
extends MEPlugin
    This is used to implement a new analysis code in the model editor. MECodePlugins contain all the functions common between analysis code plugins.

    The following is an example implementation of submitModel(com.cafean.client.analysis.AbstractModel, boolean). 

      public void submitModel(AbstractModel model) 
  {
      File tmpFile;
      File tmpSaveFile;
      try {
           tmpFile = File.createTempFile("snap",".inp");
           tmpSaveFile = File.createTempFile("snap",".sam");
      } catch( java.io.IOException ioe ) {
          ioe.printStackTrace();
          OptionPane.showMessageDialog( MainFrame.instance,
                                         "Unable to create required temporary files.",
                                         "Submit Failed",
                                         OptionPane.ERROR_MESSAGE );
          return;
      }
      
      String oldSaveName = model.getSaveFileName();
      model.setSaveFileName( tmpSaveFile.getPath() );
      model.saveModel(); 
      model.setSaveFileName( oldSaveName );
      
      boolean success = exportASCII( model, tmpFile );
      
      if( success ) {
          SubmitDialog dialog = new SubmitDialog( MainFrame.instance,
                                                  MainFrame.instance.getOrb(),
                                                  getPluginId(),
                                                  tmpFile,
                                                  tmpSaveFile,
                                                  MainFrame.instance.getPrefs());
          dialog.setVisible(true);
      }
      tmpFile.delete();
      tmpSaveFile.delete();    
  }

      • createSubSystemIntegrator

        public SubsystemIntegrator createSubSystemIntegrator​(AbstractSubSystem source,
                                                     AbstractSubSystem target)
        This factory method is used to create plug-in specific sub-system integrator objects. The default implementation of this method returns null to indicate that sub-system integration is not supported by this plug-in.

        This method allows API users to interact with the sub-system integration process without directly referencing plug-in classes.

        Parameters:
        source - the AbstractSubSystem that is the source of the new components that will be used in the integration.
        target - the AbstractSubSystem that contains the components that will be removed and replaced by the integration.
        Returns:
        a SubsystemIntegrator object that has been created to import the contents of the source sub-system into the target sub-system.

      • getRecentFilesID

        public java.lang.String getRecentFilesID()
        Retrieves the plug-in id of the code plug-in with which to to store this plug-in's recent files list entries. This can be used by a plug-in to place its recent entries into the "Recent Files" sub-menu of another plug-in rather than displaying a separate sub-menu for each plug-in in a closely tied set of plug-ins.

        NOTE: Recent files entries will only be shown for recent files ids that correspond to valid code plug-in id.

        The base implementation simply returns MEPlugin.getPluginId().

        Returns:
        a String containing this plug-in's recent files id

      • getLabel

        public java.lang.String getLabel()
        Retrieves a short string that describes a singular unit of this plugin. This is used as the label associated with this plugin in the new file dialog. The default is the ID of the plugin followed by the word "model".

      • getLabelPlural

        public java.lang.String getLabelPlural()
        Retrieves a short string that describes multiple units of this plugin. This is used as the label associated with this plugin in the navigator. The default is the ID of the plugin followed by the word "models".
